Add `setAttr(_drawer, 'aria-hidden', 'true')` when the drawer is closed and remove the attribute when opened, e.g.:

```javascript
function open() {
  setAttr(_drawer, 'aria-hidden', 'false');
  // …
}
function close() {
  setAttr(_drawer, 'aria-hidden', 'true');
  // …
}
```

---

Ensure the drawer always has an `id` (e.g., `id="nav-drawer"` in markup) or generate one in script and set `aria-controls` on the trigger:

```javascript
if (!_drawer.id) _drawer.id = shortId('nav-drawer');
setAttr(_trigger, 'aria-controls', _drawer.id);
```

---

Remove the `hidden` attribute when the carousel is initialized (or when the first slide is shown):

```javascript
function init() {
  // …
  if (_trackEl) _trackEl.removeAttribute('hidden');
  // …
}
```

---

Update the play/pause handler to toggle `aria-pressed`:

```javascript
function _onToggleClick() {
  const next = _playing ? 'month' : 'year';
  setPeriod(next);
  setAttr(_playBtn, 'aria-pressed', String(!_playing));
}
```

---

Add a hidden live region and update it whenever the count changes:

```javascript
function _updateCountBadge(count) {
  _countBadge.textContent = String(count);
  _countBadge.setAttribute('aria-label', `${count} product${count!==1?'s':''}`);
  liveRegion.announce(`${count} product${count!==1?'s':''} shown`);
}
```

---

Assign `aria-controls` to the element that contains the price values (e.g., `#pricing-cards`):

```javascript
if (_toggleEl && _toggleTrack) {
  setAttr(_toggleEl, 'aria-controls', 'pricing-cards');
}
```

---

Ensure each panel has `role="region"` (already set in parser, but verify it remains after dynamic changes) or add it explicitly when opening:

```javascript
function open(item) {
  setAttr(item.panel, 'role', 'region');
  // …
}
```

---

After applying filters, announce the result count:

```javascript
function applyFilters() {
  // existing filter logic …
  liveRegion.announce(`${visibleCount} product${visibleCount!==1?'s':''} displayed`);
}
```

---

Add an announcement when opening:

```javascript
function _openInstance(inst) {
  // existing code …
  liveRegion.announce(`Menu ${inst.trigger.textContent.trim()} opened`);
}
```

---

When creating the error element, also set `aria-describedby` on the input:

```javascript
function bind(field, rules) {
  // …
  const errorEl = _getOrCreateErrorEl(field);
  setAttr(field, 'aria-describedby', errorEl.id);
  // …
}
```

